news.title: Jaipur: RHB earns Rs 22 crore after selling 266 shops in Jhulelal market
news.para: The RHB not only developed permanent shops for Tibetans, but also earned a revenue of Rs 22 crore from the market, which was redundant.

news.title: Critical repairs of Mumbai's old buildings on hold since July 2021
news.para: After MLA Amin Patel complained to housing minister Jitendra Awhad, steps are being taken and Rs 70 crore has been ordered to be released, raising hopes of the critical repair work being resumed.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to demolish illegal buildings near IAF ammunition depot
news.para: "All under-construction buildings will be served notices and demolition squads will closely monitor the daily reports,” said additional commissioner Dr Vaishali Sharma.

news.title: Construction workers move SC seeking ex-gratia for daily wagers
news.para: ​Blanket ban on construction activities, without identifying and excluding the ones which do not contribute towards air pollution is "irrational, arbitrary and whimsical", said the petition filed by National Campaign Committee for Central Legislation on Construction Labour.

news.title: 'Anywhere property registration' policy could see revival in Karnataka
news.para: First introduced in 2013, the policy has been propagated by successive governments as a move to ease property registration pangs of house owners.

news.title: Delhi: Construction halted, but dust flies in face of ban
news.para: Though the municipal corporations and government agencies claim to have stepped up efforts and issued challans for not following the norms to control dust, TOI saw construction material and dug up soil lying in the open and dust flying when it visited a few sites.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP starts issuing property plan approvals; realtors may go to court
news.para: However, the ordinance is likely to lead to a fresh round of legal battle as a section of developers and property buyers may move the high court against the policy.

news.title: Net leasing of office space in seven cities to reach 90-95% of pre-covid level in FY23: Report
news.para: "Net leasing of commercial office space (Grade-A) will reach 90-95 per cent of the pre-pandemic level next fiscal, up from an estimated 70-75 per cent in the current one, with a return to office gathering steam and new hiring picking up strongly," it said in a statement.

news.title: ED seeks SC clarification on custodial interrogation of ex-Unitech promoters
news.para: ​The probe agency which is investigating money laundering charges against the ex-promoters said that in view of new evidence which has been found against the Chandra brothers, it needs to confront them and if required formally arrest them.

news.title: SAT allows PNB Housing Finance to withdraw appeal in Carlyle deal
news.para: ​Relating to the application filed by the company before the Securities Appellate Tribunal, seeking permission to withdraw the appeal, SAT in its hearing on November 16, 2021 allowed the company to withdraw its appeal, PNB Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Haryana TCP department orders cancellation of Brahma City's licence
news.para: “The director, town and country planning, is directed to proceed against the developer as per provisions of the Act 1975, especially as contained in Sections 8 and 10 of the Act 1975,” according to the order passed by A K Singh, principal secretary, department of town and country planning, Haryana.

news.title: Workspace bets on flexible leases to navigate post-pandemic market
news.para: Office space operators are facing a bumpy road to recovery after battling lower rental levels and steep valuation declines in the wake of the pandemic when clients shifted to remote working or downsized or vacated spaces.

news.title: European Central Bank sees rising risk that housing bubble will burst
news.para: With families building up savings during pandemic and increasingly working from home, demand for property is on the rise, pushing house price growth to over 7%, its fastest rate since 2005.

news.title: Bombay HC allows DHFL's plea to discharge its name from CBI investigation
news.para: DHFL has argued that since it had been taken over by Piramal Capital & Housing Finance Ltd, it should be absolved from all earlier liabilities.

news.title: ED conducts raids against Supertech Group in NCR
news.para: The Supreme Court had on August 31 ordered the demolition of the Noida located twin towers of the Supertech Group, which had come up in violation of building bylaws.
